From: jeremy@myfacetwittertube.com
Subject: [PATCH] transformers/integrations/moe: force fallback grouped_mm on ROCm

torch._grouped_mm and torch.nn.functional.grouped_mm have no ROCm backend
as of torch 2.9.1+rocm6.4. Calling them raises:

    RuntimeError: grouped gemm is not supported on ROCM

`_can_use_grouped_mm` checks `weight.device.type == "cuda"` to gate the CUDA
fast path, but ROCm/HIP devices also report device.type=="cuda" in PyTorch.
The function then calls `torch.cuda.get_device_capability` which on AMD
returns a uarch tuple and passes the >=(8,0) check, so `_can_use_grouped_mm`
returns True and we hit the unimplemented op.

This patch detects ROCm via `torch.version.hip` inside the cuda branch and
returns False, forcing the loop-based `_grouped_mm_fallback` path that
already exists in the same file.

Affects all MoE models with the new transformers grouped-MoE path
(GLM-4.7-Flash, GPT-OSS-20B, Llama-4 Scout/Maverick, Qwen3-30B-A3B, etc.).

Apply with:
  cd /path/to/transformers && git apply 0002-transformers-disable-grouped-mm-on-rocm.patch

Or directly to a venv install:
  patch /path/to/.venv/lib/python*/site-packages/transformers/integrations/moe.py < 0002-...

---
 src/transformers/integrations/moe.py | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/transformers/integrations/moe.py b/src/transformers/integrations/moe.py
@@ -287,6 +287,11 @@ def _can_use_grouped_mm(input, weight, offs):
     # On CUDA, `grouped_mm` availability also depends on GPU compute capability:
     # `torch.nn.functional.grouped_mm` in torch>=2.10 and `torch._grouped_mm` in torch>=2.9 support SM80+
     # but older `torch._grouped_mm` requires SM90+.
     if weight.device.type == "cuda":
+        # ROCm/HIP advertises device.type=="cuda" but torch._grouped_mm has no
+        # ROCm backend yet (raises "grouped gemm is not supported on ROCM").
+        # Force fallback so MoE forward works on AMD GPUs.
+        if getattr(torch.version, "hip", None) is not None:
+            return False
         if hasattr(torch.nn.functional, "grouped_mm"):
             return torch.cuda.get_device_capability(weight.device) >= (8, 0)
         if hasattr(torch, "_grouped_mm"):
